quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  55,1,IT IS the Merciful
  55,2,who has taught the Koran
  55,3,He created man
  55,4,and taught him articulate speech
  55,5,The sun and the moon pursue their ordered course
  55,6,The plants and the trees bow down in adoration
  55,7,The heaven He raised on high and set the Balance of all things
  55,8,that you might not transgress that Balance
  55,9,"Give just weight and full measure, and do not cheat the Balance"
  55,10,And the earth He laid for His creatures
  55,11,with all its fruits and blossom-bearing palm
  55,12,chaff-covered grain and scented herbs
  55,13,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you² deny
  55,14,He created man from potter‘s clay
  55,15,and the jinn from smokeless fire
  55,16,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,17,"The Lord of the two easts³ is He, and the Lord of the two wests"
  55,18,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,19,"He has let loose the two seas:⁴ they meet one another"
  55,20,Yet between them stands a barrier which they cannot overrun
  55,21,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,22,Pearls and corals come out from both
  55,23,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,24,His are the ships that sail like mountains upon the ocean
  55,25,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny